Jakadan Amurka ya zargi China da "ta'addanci da tallar aikin yi"
Makon daya bayan jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani talla na shafi hudu a jaridar Amurka ta yau da kullum game da amfanin yau da kullum na cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da kafofin watsa labarai na Amurka don yada farfaganda.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi nuni da wani shafi da jaridar China Daily ta biya a ranar Laraba a cikin Des Moines Register, jaridar da ke da babbar murya a jihar Iowa, bayan da aka zargi China da tsoma baki a zaben da aka yi a ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, wanda China ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi na cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka bayyana wa Reuters a matsayin wani sabon mataki a cikin yunkurin kara matsa lamba a kan China.
Ko da yake yana da kyau gwamnatocin ƙasashen waje su yi talla don su inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington suna faɗa cikin yaƙin kasuwanci da ke ƙaruwa, inda suke daidaita harajin da suke saka wa kayayyakin da suke shigowa.
An yi amfani da matakan da China ta dauka a farkon yakin ta'addanci don kama masu fitar da kayayyaki daga jihohi kamar Iowa saboda goyon bayan jam'iyyun Republican na Trump, masana na China da Amurka sun bayyana.
Jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, kuma babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona na kasar Sin, Terry Branstad, ya ce Beijing ta cutar da ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni.
A cikin wata sanarwa da aka wallafa a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register a ranar Lahadi, Branstad ya ce: 'Sai yanzu China ta ninka ta da ta yi amfani da tallace-tallace na gaggawa a cikin jaridarmu mai 'yanci.'
"A cikin yada farfagandarsu, gwamnatin China tana amfani da kyawawan halaye na 'yancin faɗar albarkacin baki da kuma aikin jarida na Amurka ta hanyar sanya tallan da take biya a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A gefe guda, akwai 'yan murya kaɗan a cikin titunan Beijing kuma ba su ga ra'ayoyi daban-daban da jama'ar China za su iya yi game da yanayin tattalin arzikin China da ke damunsu ba, saboda kafofin watsa labarai suna ƙarƙashin ikon jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin", in ji shi.
